<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <meta name="csrf-token" content="<%= csrfToken %>">
    <%- include('../partials/head-assets') %>
    <script src="/js/theme-toggle.js" defer></script>
    <script src="/js/hardware-mfa-module.js" defer></script>
</head>

<body class="<%= (user && user.preferences && user.preferences.nightMode) ? 'dark-mode' : '' %>">
    <%- include('../partials/theme-toggle') %>
    <div
        class="container mt-5 mb-5"
        id="hardware-mfa-module-root"
        data-hardware-mfa-overview-endpoint="/api/hardware-mfa/overview"
        data-hardware-mfa-register-options-endpoint="/api/hardware-mfa/register/options"
        data-hardware-mfa-register-verify-endpoint="/api/hardware-mfa/register/verify"
        data-hardware-mfa-pki-register-endpoint="/api/hardware-mfa/pki/register-current"
        data-hardware-mfa-challenge-endpoint="/api/hardware-mfa/challenge"
        data-hardware-mfa-verify-endpoint="/api/hardware-mfa/verify"
        data-hardware-mfa-revoke-endpoint="/api/hardware-mfa/revoke">
        <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4 flex-wrap gap-3">
            <div>
                <h1 class="notes-title mb-1">Hardware-Backed MFA Module</h1>
                <p class="text-muted mb-2">A research workspace for strong-factor step-up assurance that prefers hardware tokens and PKI certificates over weaker software-only second factors.</p>
                <p class="text-muted mb-0">Inspect the current session assurance, review registered authenticators, and perform real hardware-backed step-up flows so sensitive actions can require strong evidence before execution.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="d-flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
                <a href="/research" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Back to Research</a>
                <a href="/mission-assurance/module" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Open Mission Access Assurance Module</a>
                <a href="/security/module" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Open Security Operations Module</a>
                <a href="/notes" class="btn btn-secondary">Back to Notes</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-3 mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Session Assurance</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1" id="hardware-mfa-session-badge">Not verified</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Current step-up state for the signed-in session.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Active Method</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1 fs-3" id="hardware-mfa-method-badge">None</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Most recent strong factor used for this session.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Registered Factors</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1" id="hardware-mfa-factor-count">0</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">Hardware token and PKI factors currently available.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xl-3">
                <div class="card research-summary-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Protected Actions</p>
                        <p class="display-6 mb-1" id="hardware-mfa-sensitive-count">0</p>
                        <p class="text-muted mb-0">High-impact actions that require hardware-first step-up.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card automation-card mb-4">
            <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column flex-xl-row justify-content-between align-items-xl-center gap-3">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="h5 mb-1">Hardware-First Controls</h2>
                    <p class="text-muted mb-1">Use this module to compare Hardware token and PKI-backed step-up options, inspect the active challenge, and clear elevated assurance when the operation is complete.</p>
                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0">The goal is to make high-risk approval flows depend on something physically possessed or certificate-bound, not just a password or an SMS code.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="d-flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
                    <button type="button" id="hardware-mfa-register-btn" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Register Security Key</button>
                    <button type="button" id="hardware-mfa-register-pki-btn" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Register Current PKI Cert</button>
                    <button type="button" id="hardware-mfa-refresh-btn" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Refresh Module</button>
                    <button type="button" id="hardware-mfa-revoke-btn" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Revoke Step-Up</button>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body pt-0">
                <div id="hardware-mfa-status"></div>
                <p class="text-muted small mt-3 mb-0" id="hardware-mfa-transport-status">Loading transport security posture...</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4 mb-4">
            <div class="col-xl-5">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Profile</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Current Session Context</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">This is the current profile the server is evaluating before it allows a sensitive action to proceed.</p>
                        <div id="hardware-mfa-session-summary"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-7">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Factors</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Registered Hardware-First Authenticators</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">Each registered factor represents a stronger step-up path than a software-only second factor.</p>
                        <div id="hardware-mfa-authenticator-grid" class="row g-3"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row g-4 mb-4">
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Challenge</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Challenge And Verify</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">Start a hardware-backed challenge, then verify it with a browser WebAuthn security-key assertion or a verified PKI client certificate.</p>
                        <form id="hardware-mfa-form" class="row g-3">
                            <div class="col-12">
                                <label for="hardware-mfa-register-label" class="form-label">Security key label</label>
                                <input type="text" class="form-control" id="hardware-mfa-register-label" placeholder="Example: YubiKey 5 NFC">
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                <label for="hardware-mfa-method-select" class="form-label">Method</label>
                                <select id="hardware-mfa-method-select" class="form-select">
                                    <option value="">Loading methods...</option>
                                </select>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-end">
                                <button type="button" id="hardware-mfa-start-btn" class="btn btn-dark w-100">Start Challenge</button>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-12">
                                <label for="hardware-mfa-challenge-id" class="form-label">Challenge ID</label>
                                <input type="text" class="form-control" id="hardware-mfa-challenge-id" readonly>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-12">
                                <label for="hardware-mfa-response" class="form-label">Verification response</label>
                                <input type="text" class="form-control" id="hardware-mfa-response" placeholder="Used only for development simulation or manual PKI fallback flows.">
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-12">
                                <button type="button" id="hardware-mfa-verify-btn" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Verify Challenge</button>
                            </div>
                        </form>
                        <div class="playwright-prereq-card mt-3">
                            <p class="research-kicker mb-2">Active challenge instructions</p>
                            <p class="text-muted mb-0" id="hardware-mfa-challenge-instructions">Start a challenge to see the expected proof for the current method.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-xl-6">
                <div class="card automation-card h-100">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <span class="research-kicker">Policy</span>
                        <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Protected Actions</h2>
                        <p class="text-muted small mb-3">These actions are strong candidates for hardware-first step-up because they carry operational or governance risk.</p>
                        <div id="hardware-mfa-sensitive-actions" class="d-flex flex-column gap-3"></div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card automation-card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <span class="research-kicker">Principles</span>
                <h2 class="h4 mt-2 mb-1">Hardware-First MFA Guidance</h2>
                <p class="text-muted small mb-3">The module treats hardware presence and PKI identity as the preferred assurance path for sensitive workflows.</p>
                <div id="hardware-mfa-principles" class="row g-3"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
